<!-- Why crop-specific section -->
<section class="section">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="two-col-layout">
            <div>
                <span class="section-eyebrow">The DripSmart Difference</span>
                <h2>Generic Irrigation Is Leaving Money in the Field</h2>
                <p>Most irrigation systems are designed for "average" conditions. But your almond orchard isn't average. Your soil isn't average. Your water isn't average.</p>
                <p style="margin-top:16px;">DripSmart's crop-specific engineering accounts for root architecture, evapotranspiration curves, disease pressure, harvest operations, and your specific soil profile to deliver a system that's custom-built for your crop and your ground.</p>
                <ul class="check-list" style="margin-top:24px;">
                    <li>Free agronomic site assessment before system design</li>
                    <li>Crop-specific emitter spacing and flow rate selection</li>
                    <li>Root zone modeling using your soil texture data</li>
                    <li>Integration with crop ET models and weather forecasting</li>
                    <li>Seasonal calibration support from certified agronomists</li>
                </ul>
                <a href="/contact" class="btn-primary" style="margin-top:28px;display:inline-block;">Request a Site Assessment</a>
            </div>
            <div style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:20px;">
                <div class="info-card">
                    <div class="info-card-icon"><i data-lucide="microscope"></i></div>
                    <h3>Soil Science First</h3>
                    <p>Every DripSmart design starts with soil texture, infiltration rate, and rooting depth analysis — inputs that determine lateral spacing, emitter flow, and cycle frequency.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="info-card">
                    <div class="info-card-icon"><i data-lucide="bar-chart-2"></i></div>
                    <h3>ET-Based Scheduling</h3>
                    <p>Our DripSphere OS platform integrates CIMIS and AZMET ET data to automatically adjust irrigation schedules as weather and crop stage evolve through the season.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="info-card">
                    <div class="info-card-icon"><i data-lucide="sprout"></i></div>
                    <h3>Crop-Stage Precision</h3>
                    <p>From germination through harvest, DripSmart systems adapt to the water and nutrient demands of each crop growth stage — maximizing yield while minimizing waste.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

